✅ 1. Declaration + Initialization (Most common)
int[] arr = {10, 20, 30, 40};

✅ 2. Using new keyword with values
int[] arr = new int[] {10, 20, 30, 40};

✅ 3. Create an empty array and assign values later
int[] arr = new int[4];
arr[0] = 10;
arr[1] = 20;

✅ 4. Dynamic initialization using loop
int[] arr = new int[5];
for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    arr[i] = i * 2;
}